    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-04-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <head>151. Memorandum From Lay to the <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d151fn1">Source: Transmits a memorandum from
                            <persName corresp="#p_QDA_1">Quarles</persName> to the <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> on “Status of Military Mobilization Base
                        Program.” Secret. 2 pp. NARA, <gloss target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, <gloss
                            target="#t_SP_1">S/P</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files:
                        Lot 62 D 1, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> 5810, 5906.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1959-04-21">April 21, 1959</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d151-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d151-1"/>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Status of Military Mobilization Base Program</item>
                </list>
                <list type="references">
                    <head>REFERENCES</head>
                    <item>A. <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> 5810/1</item>
                    <item>B. <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 2019</item>
                </list>
                <p>The enclosed memorandum on the subject from the Deputy Secretary of Defense,
                    prepared pursuant to <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 2019–<hi
                        rend="italic">b</hi>–(1) <pb facs="0799" n="694" type="typeset"
                        xml:id="pg_694"/> and –(2), is transmitted herewith for the information of
                    the National Security Council.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LJS_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">James S. Lay, Jr.</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Executive Secretary</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>cc: The Secretary of the Treasury</p>
                    <p>The Director, Bureau of the Budget</p>
                    <p>The Chairman, Joint Chiefs of Staff</p>
                    <p>The Director of Central Intelligence</p>
                </postscript>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <note rend="inline">
                        <hi rend="strong">Enclosure</hi>
                    </note>
                    <head>Memorandum From <persName corresp="#p_QDA_1">Quarles</persName> to
                        Lay</head>
                    <pb facs="d151-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d151-2"/>
                    <list type="subject">
                        <head>SUBJECT</head>
                        <item>Status of Military Mobilization Base Program (U)</item>
                    </list>
                    <p>
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 2019 requires that the
                        Department of Defense report to the National Security Council on
                        developments in the review of its Mobilization Base planning concepts.</p>
                    <p>In reference to paragraph <hi rend="italic">b</hi>–(1) of <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 2019, the Department of Defense
                        is now reviewing the validity of the assumption of a mobilization period of
                        six months prior to D-Day. The results of this review will be incorporated
                        into our recommendations to be made in connection with the current review of
                        Basic National Security Policy (<gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                        5810/1).</p>
                    <p>In reference to paragraph <hi rend="italic">b</hi>–(2), the Department of
                        Defense, in cooperation with the Office of Civil and Defense Mobilization,
                        has just completed the first in a series of hazard probability studies for
                        use in identifying logistics problems which might reasonably be predicted in
                        connection with the initial phase of a General War. These studies constitute
                        an important initial step in giving us a capability for taking bomb damage
                        into account in future mobilization base planning.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_QDA_1">
                                <hi rend="strong">/s/ Donald A. Quarles</hi>
                            </persName>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Deputy</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
